ENTRY            A0407   20260129   20260327   20260327       A130
SUBENT        A0407001   20260129   20260327   20260327       A130
BIB                 15         45
TITLE      Fragmentation of unstable neutron-rich oxygen beams
AUTHOR     (A.Leistenschneider, T.Aumann, K.Boretzky, L.F.Canto,
           B.V.Carlson, D.Cortina, U.Datta-Pramanik, Th.W.Eize,
           H.Emling, H.Geissel, A.Gruenschloss, K.Helariutta,
           M.Hellstroem, M.S.Hussein, S.Ilievski, K.L.Jones,
           J.V.Kratz, R.Kulessa, Le-Hong-Khiem, E.Lubkiewicz,
           G.Muenzenberg, R.Palit, P.Reiter, C.Scheidenberger,
           K.-H.Schimdt, H.Simon, K.Suemmerer, E.Wajda, W.Walus)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,65,064607,2002)
REL-REF    (N,,D.L.Olson+,J,PR/C,24,1529,1981) - Measurements of
           fragment-production cross sections have been made
           with 18O projectiles of 1.7 GeV/nucleon incident upon
           targets of Be, C, Al, Ti, Cu, Sn, W, Pb, and U.
INSTITUTE  (2GERFRK,2GERGSI,2GERMNZ,3BZLUFR,3BZLITA,3BZLUSP,
           3POLUJK,2GERLMU,2GERTHD)
FACILITY   (SYNCH,2GERGSI)
INC-SOURCE Secondary beams of (17-21)O ions were produced in a
           fragmentation reaction of a primary 40Ar beam
           delivered by the synchrotron SIS at GSI, Darmstadt.
           The secondary oxygen beams were separated in the
           fragment separator FRS operated at three different
           magnetic field settings optimized for (17,18)O,
            (19,20)O, and (21,22)O.
SAMPLE     Natural carbon target (0.573 g/cm2).
DETECTOR   (SCIN,SI) The detection system for the fragments
           consisted of two silicon detectors (one of them being
           position sensitive), a dipole magnet with a large
           gap of 0.5 m x 31.2 m, three scintillating fiber
           detectors, and a time-of-flight wall consisting of an
           array of 20 organic scintillation detectors, each one
           of 2000 x 100 x 10 mm3 size and placed about 11 m
           downstream from the target.
CORRECTION The main correction factor arises from the finite
           acceptance of the detector system for some of the
           fragments.
METHOD     (TOF,OLMS)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
ADD-RES    (COMP) The empirical EPAX parametrization and
           abrasion-ablation model.
STATUS     (TABLE,,A.Leistenschneider+,J,PR/C,65,064607,2002)
                                                 Table I.
HISTORY    (20020626C)
           (20021217U) Last checking has been done.
           (20260129A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           ERR-T -> DATA-ERR.
ENDBIB              45
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           48
